reviewText: This video is a gift for my husband for Christmas. So I can't really give a review about these episodes. However, if these episodes are anything like the first four seasons I'm sure it will not disappoint. Jim Belushi and the Gang are extremely entertaining and funny.

We've always had issues with According to Jim being fuzzy for the first few seconds after starting or restarting the video. However, Season 5 is the worst.  In nearly rvery episode, the picture will just suddenly go out of focus and/or freeze. It's not our Internet speed. No other video on Amazon or Netflix does it,  only Jim. I'm about to ask for a refund.

Harmless, funny entertainment.  Stars seem to enjoy playing their parts.  Larry Joe Campbell is refreshing to watch.  It's nice to see an overweight person cast in an important role on a well-known sitcom.
Good season, I would recommend getting it. According to Jim was a good show, to bad it's not on anymore.

So many comedy's now days aim at adults only. This is one that's completely safe and teaches some good lessons for the family. Dad isn't perfect but isn't an idiot like on some many other so called family comedies. He's a bit childish at times but always means well. Thats why I love this show and look forward to the remaining seasons being available soon.
